<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>06 June 2008</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Plymouth Marine Laboratory (WSC017)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Plymouth Marine Laboratory</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (PML) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is a world-class, independent research laboratory engaged in marine environmental </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">research across a wide range of topics of interest and relevance to society.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  It was established in 2002 as a company limited by guarantee with charitable status.  Prior to this it was wholly owned by the Natural Environment Research Council.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This evide</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nce is submitted by PML and represents its independent views.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In preparing this response it was felt valuable to consider </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> statistics </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">relating to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> female science staff employment and students at PML</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, as well as consider the proportion of female staff</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> across the grade structure.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  Of the current scie</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ntific staff employed at PML, 44%</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are female and of the current PhD students</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> 47</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">% are female.  These percentages have remained fairly constant over the last three years. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Whilst the percentage of female/male </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">scientific </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">staff is broadly equivalent, there are significant differences at both ends of the grade structure. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">emale </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">employees </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mak</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> up 100% of the lowest technician grade and 75% of the junior scientist level</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, whereas </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at the two highest grades they represent one third and one quarter, respectively, of the community</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Responses to specific questions raised are as follows:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Why do numbers of women in STEM academic careers decline further up the career ladder? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The main reason that women in STEM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">academic careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> decline further up the career ladder is that the time for advancing a career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> often</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> coincides with having children.  Women tend to take on the main role in rearing children and domestic/family management.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Women often tend to be the carers of elderly relatives.  With life expectancy increasing, this also adds to the problem of greater family responsibilities.</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  Science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> as a career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> requir</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">es complete dedication and thus it is difficult to manage/juggle all th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e responsibilities.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  To progress </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">within the science community requires a lot of travelling to conferences and meeting</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and hence it is difficult to meet these demands as well as those of managing a family at the same time.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Whilst it is possible </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as a female scientist </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to take a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> career break to raise a family</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, this does have a negative impact in terms of a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">causing a hiatus in her publication record.  T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">his problem is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">exacerbate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">d on returning to work as, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">v</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ery often</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a female scientist with children wi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ll return on a part-time basis and therefore </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">does not have sufficient time to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">publish </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as prolifically as her male counterparts.  A </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">scientist’s publication record and hence H index</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(a measure of both the productivity and impact of the published work of a sc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ientist)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are fundamental to success, affecting the ability to secure research funding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> promotion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in the future</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The “glass ceiling”, a term often used in the corporate world, can also exist in the scientific environment, with scientifi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">c </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">leadership dominated by males</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  There are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> few</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> female</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> role models</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">particularly those juggling family and career, in senior scientific positions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in the UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, to provide mentoring</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  That said, the appointment of Dr Jackie Hunter as the new Chief Executive of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the Biotechnology &amp; Biological Sciences Council </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(BBSRC) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">earlier this summer is welcome.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">When women leave academia, what careers do they transition into? What are the consequences of scientifically trained women applying their skills in different </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">employment sectors?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women often transi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">tion to very successful careers in senior management/consultancy roles.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Science training brings excellent skills in logical and critical thinking and these are valuable in a number of careers.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">What should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">universities and the higher education sector do to retain women graduates and PhD students in academic careers? Are there examples of good practice?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:22.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There needs to be a cultural shift in encouraging gender balance throughout the workplace and at all level</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  Where there are women in senior scientific roles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or science leadership roles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, they could be engaged to act as mentors.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.75pt; padding-left:17.25pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Flexible employment practices and child care support are also important.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.75pt; padding-left:17.25pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There needs to be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">greater </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ecognition of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a woma</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n’s circumstances (career break/family) when assessing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">proposals (publication track records) or determining promotion.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.75pt; padding-left:17.25pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Establish </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">schemes, such as the Royal Society’s Dorothy Hodgkin Fellowship scheme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> see</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">http://royalsociety.org/grants/schemes/dorothy-hodgkin/</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, which provides funding for scientists </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at an early stage of their research career who require a flexible working pattern due to personal circumstances such as parenting</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, etc.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; margin:0pt; padding-bottom:1pt; padding-left:4pt; padding-right:4pt; padding-top:1pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">What role should the Government have in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.75pt; padding-left:17.25pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Government needs to work towards developing a cultural shift in: </span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Encouraging gender balance throughout the workplace and at all levels. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Encouraging men to take on more responsibility and sharing in domestic and family affairs.  </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.75pt; padding-left:17.25pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Obtain views/assistance from women in senior scientific </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or science leadership </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">roles, e.g. the Chief Scientific Advisor to the EU (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Prof. Anne Glove</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r, CBE, FRSE).</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18.75pt; padding-left:17.25pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Government policy on c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">hild care provision</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> needs to be aligned, e.g. the move towards more highly qualified nursery staff could lead to a substantial increase in child care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, resulting in fewer women being able to afford child care and thus</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> not able to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> return to their careers.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>